<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Calamagrostis</i> <i>canadensis</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Achillea</i> <i>millefolium</i>, <i>Aconitum</i> <i>columbianum</i>, <i>Allium</i> <i>validum</i>, <i>Bistorta</i> <i>bistortoides</i>, <i>Caltha</i> <i>leptosepala</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>utriculata</i>, <i>Dodecatheon</i> <i>jeffreyi</i>, <i>Epilobium</i> <i>ciliatum</i>, <i>Glyceria</i> <i>striata</i>, <i>Hordeum</i> <i>brachyantherum</i>, <i>Hypericum</i> <i>anagalloides</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>oblongifolius</i>, <i>Lupinus</i> <i>latifolius</i>, <i>Mimulus</i> <i>guttatus</i>, <i>Mimulus</i> <i>primuloides</i>, <i>Phleum</i> <i>alpinum</i>, <i>Senecio</i> <i>triangularis</i>, <i>Solidago</i> <i>canadensis</i>, <i>Sphenosciadium</i> <i>capitellatum</i>, <i>Symphyotrichum</i> <i>spathulatum</i>, <i>Thalictrum</i> <i>fendleri</i> and <i>Veratrum</i> <i>californicum</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Pinus</i> <i>contorta</i> ssp. <i>murrayana</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Calamagrostis canadensis</i> > 50% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Montane to subalpine wet meadows, basins, moist forest openings, floodplains of small streams, terraces, lakeshores. Soils are usually poorly drained loams and clays that may be mucky. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Calamagrostis canadensis</i> as a FACW+ plant. </div>
</div>

        
