<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fluvial processes primarily maintain the alliance rather than fire<i>. Calamagrostis canadensis </i>sprouts from surviving rhizomes when fires occur, and it can establish after burns by wind-dispersed seeds. Light fires tend to increase the abundance of this reed grass (Tesky 1992a) in some cases.</div>
